<item>
            <title>[PDFBOX-2521] Don&apos;t throw IOException if stream length is missing in lenient mode</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/PDFBOX-2521</link>
                <project id="12310760" key="PDFBOX">PDFBox</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The non-sequential parser throws an IOException if the lenght of a stream is missing. This should be avoided in lenient mode, escpacially as the parser checks the length afterwards add uses the fallback readUntilEnd if the length is invalid.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
