                            <comment id="14224456" author="ssteiner1" created="Tue, 25 Nov 2014 12:09:07 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Added patch to fix error&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14225868" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 26 Nov 2014 07:43:29 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=ssteiner1&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;ssteiner1&quot;&gt;ssteiner1&lt;/a&gt; Thanks for the patch. It indicates that your pdf has a malformed hybrid xref table, or PDFBox has an issue reading that correct. Your patch isn&apos;t optimal, it just guesses that something may be wrong. I&apos;d like to improve the parser itself to self detect such cases, so that we know that something is wrong. Is there any chance to share the relevant parts of the pdf or better to send me the pdf?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14226138" author="ssteiner1" created="Wed, 26 Nov 2014 12:44:53 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Pdf with issue&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14226666" author="lehmi" created="Wed, 26 Nov 2014 19:08:12 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;The pdf is malformed and the self repair mechnism doesn&apos;t detect it. We have to improve that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
